title: Fannin County offense leads Rebels past Lumpkin County
text:
Saturday October 10th, 2015 4:20AM Posted 8:16AM on Saturday 10th October 2015 ( 3 hours from now ) Fannin County offense leads Rebels past Lumpkin County By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles 2015 High school football rankings 2015 High School Football region standings WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night VIDEO: Brown, Lanier defense spark Longhorns to tough win over GHS 
DAHLONEGA — Fannin County's offense stormed out of the gates and helped the Rebels pull out a 41-35 win over Lumpkin County on Friday in Dahlonega. 
Fannin County (3-3, 1-1 Region 7-AAA) put up 34 points in the first half -- largely behind the arm of quarterback Brad Davis, who passed for 416 yards before the interval. Davis completed scoring passes to three different receivers in the first half -- Jacob Reece, Christian Resendiz and Cooper Earls all catching touchdown passes. 
Lumpkin County battled to get back into the contest, Austin Pierce catching a touchdown pass from Chandler Woodham and Zach Matthews returning a kickoff 87 yards for a score as the Indians (2-5, 0-3) pulled within 34-14 at the half. Lumpkin then scored 14 unanswered points -- a Matthews run and a blocked punt for a score -- in the third quarter to pull within 34-28. 
But Fannin responded through a 39-yard touchdown run from Jack Roper for a 41-28 advantage that Lumpkin could not overhaul despite another late touchdown. 
Fannin County will play host to Dawson County next week. 
Lumpkin County will travel to Banks County next week. Associated Categories : Sports , High School Sports , Friday Game Night Associated Tags : High school football, Lumpkin County football, Fannin County football © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
